  <div class="column_holder">
    <h1>
      <img alt="JOBS" src="/images/headers/pf_heading/dynamicimage.aspx?text=JOBS" />
    </h1>
    <div class="column_heading">
      <span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblTop"><p>GRIN is constantly looking for talented people. All available positions are listed below. Apply via the form or by e-mail.  If you are interested in a position that isn&rsquo;t listed, please send your CV via e-mail to jobs@grin.se.</p></span></div>
    <div class="column_sep">
      <img src="img/jobs/jobs_open_sep.png" alt="Open positions" /></div>
    
    
      <div class="column_content">
        <h1>
          <img alt="Friday 22 August 2008" src="/images/headers/pf_small/dynamicimage.aspx?text=Friday 22 August 2008" />
        </h1>
        <h2>
          <img alt="Tools Programmer" src="/images/headers/pf_heading/dynamicimage.aspx?text=Tools Programmer" />
        </h2>
        <p>
          <span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText"><p><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText">We have an opening to join the Grin core team in Stockholm, to help with further development of our tools pipeline. Day to day work includes:<br />
</span></p>
<ul>
    <li><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText">Working closely with artists and designers while designing new tools and user-interfaces<br />
    </span></li>
    <li><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText">Supporting and extending existing systems to cope with new requirements<br />
    </span></li>
    <li><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText">Identifying studio-wide issues to improve workflow across multiple disciplines</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText">You will work closely together with artists as well as our engine department to make sure that we maintain a state of the art tools pipeline.<br />
<br />
<strong> Requirements:</strong><br />
</span></p>
<ul>
    <li><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText">Excellent object-oriented programming and debugging skills</span></li>
    <li><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText">Solid experience with one or more dynamic programming languages (Ex. Python / Ruby / Lua)</span></li>
    <li><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText">Motivated and able to work without close supervision</span></li>
    <li>Good problem solving and communication skills</li>
    <li><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText">Good user-</span>interface design skills</li>
    <li><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText">Previous experience with one or more GUI frameworks (Ex. wxWidgets / GTK / QT / WinForms)<br />
    </span></li>
</ul>
<p><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText"><strong>Pluses:</strong><br />
</span></p>
<ul>
    <li><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText">Good C and C++ skills</span></li>
    <li><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText">Experience with several popular content-creation packages (Ex. Maya / Max / Photoshop / Cubase / Final Cut)</span></li>
    <li><span id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_lblJobText">Previous experience in the game industry</span></li>
</ul></span></p>
      </div>
      <div class="column_nav">
        <span class="column_nav_cat">Contact</span>
        <p>
          Please send your application through the online form below, or by regular mail to
          our physical adress. If you prefer to send your application by email click
          <a href="&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#101;&#110;&#103;&#105;&#110;&#101;&#64;&#103;&#114;&#105;&#110;&#46;&#115;&#101;">here</a>.</p>
      </div>
